                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/14325.</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico City</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-02-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 1, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>General Benjamin Hill is in command of city during the absence of Obregon in Vera
                    Cruz. Zapatistas continue to occupy the farthest southern suburbs; they still
                    control and have cut the main city water supply. The Constitutionalists are
                    operating the Mexican Railway.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Silliman.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
